# Build context exclusions.
#
# The Dockerfile copies only package files, tsconfig, prisma/ and src/, so
# nothing secret reaches the image regardless. What this file prevents is the
# whole context being streamed to the daemon on every build — most of it
# node_modules, which on a dev machine holds platform-native binaries
# (@napi-rs/canvas, prisma engines) for the WRONG architecture when the target
# is ARM. Excluding it also guarantees `npm ci` resolves fresh inside the image.

node_modules
dist
.git
.gitignore

# Never ship real secrets into a build context.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Docs and tooling — irrelevant to the build.
*.md
docs
.claude
AUDIT_REPORT.md

# OS / editor noise
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode
.idea
*.swp
